{"title":"Review: KOM Cycling detachable GoPro mount is really the best light mount","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/06/03/review-kom-cycling-detachable-gopro-mount-is-really-the-best-light-mount/","date":1622728230000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p><span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-box-3\"></span>There are a lot of ways to put a GoPro on you or your bike, but most of them require a bit of a commitment. Meaning, once you’ve threaded or clicked the camera into place and adjusted it, that’s probably where you’re leaving it for a while. <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B084Y1Y9V5/?tag=20br-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">KOM Cycling’s latest mount</a> makes it a bit easier to grab a couple different angles.</p><p>Even better, if you use a GoPro-style mount for your headlight, it could be the fastest, easiest way to get that light on and off your bike for charging…</p><h3>KOM CM06 Quick Release GoPro Computer Mount</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/10112356/kom-outfront-cycling-computer-gopro-mount-review-06.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/10112356/kom-outfront-cycling-computer-gopro-mount-review-06.jpg\" alt=\"KOM cycling twist-off gopro mount for out front cycling computer mounts\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1200\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/10112356/kom-outfront-cycling-computer-gopro-mount-review-06.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/10112356/kom-outfront-cycling-computer-gopro-mount-review-06-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/10112356/kom-outfront-cycling-computer-gopro-mount-review-06-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.co