 the benefit? That depends on the shot you want…if we’re being honest, chest and helmet cams provide a bit better perspective for both riding and following someone. But with the latest action cameras offering incredibly good stabilization and wide angles, getting good follow-cam footage from the handlebar is entirely possible.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/10112350/kom-outfront-cycling-computer-gopro-mount-review-05.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/10112350/kom-outfront-cycling-computer-gopro-mount-review-05.jpg\" alt=\"KOM cycling twist-off gopro mount for out front cycling computer mounts\" width=\"1200\" height=\"900\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/10112350/kom-outfront-cycling-computer-gopro-mount-review-05.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/10112350/kom-outfront-cycling-computer-gopro-mount-review-05-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/10112350/kom-outfront-cycling-computer-gopro-mount-review-05-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/10112350/kom-outfront-cycling-computer-gopro-mount-review-05-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/10112350/kom-outfront-cycling-computer-gopro-mount-review-05-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/10112350/kom-outfront-cycling-computer-gopro-mount-review-05-696x522.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/10112350/kom-outfront-cycling-computer-gopro-mount-review-05-1068x801.jpg 1068w,https